  "security_notes": "ctfmon.exe is mostly a baseline process: its value is a steady identity, the logged-on user's account, a Microsoft signature, no children, and no network, so deviations are easy to see. The realistic abuse is impersonation (T1036.005), where malware borrows the obscure but familiar name from the wrong path or runs under the wrong account.\n\nAs a persistent per-user process it could also be an injection target (T1055). A ctfmon.exe that loads unusual modules, opens network connections, or spawns anything is acting outside its normal role.\n",
